                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6369/272.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Jose</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-11-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 15, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Merry acknowledges department’s telegram of 12th, and says President of Costa
                    Rica promises adherence to the Washington conventions, and states that
                    Nicaraguan Government has apologized for invasion.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
